# Motion rules — non-negotiable

Every animation, scroll-jacking, RAF loop, R3F canvas, GSAP timeline, and shader uniform must consult `useMotion()` (`src/lib/useMotion.ts`).

## Required pattern

```tsx
const { prefersReducedMotion, qualityTier, isPageVisible } = useMotion();

useEffect(() => {
  if (prefersReducedMotion) return;        // no scroll-jacking, no scrub
  if (!isPageVisible) return;              // pause when tab hidden
  if (qualityTier === "low") return;       // skip the expensive layer

  const ctx = gsap.context(() => { /* … */ }, scopeRef);
  return () => ctx.revert();
}, [prefersReducedMotion, qualityTier, isPageVisible]);
```

## Quality tier guidance

- `low`: static fallback or 1× resolution canvas, no postprocessing, no compute shader.
- `medium`: full geometry but cap pixel ratio at 1.5, disable bloom or replace with cheap glow.
- `high`: everything on.

## GSAP

- Always wrap timelines in `gsap.context(() => …, scopeRef)` and `revert()` on cleanup.
- Use named eases from `src/lib/easings.ts` (`GSAP_EASES.glide`, etc.) — no ad-hoc cubic-béziers.
- Lenis-driven scroll: prefer the helper exposed in `src/lenisStore.ts`; never instantiate Lenis twice.

## R3F

- Heavy scenes (>50k particles, postprocessing, compute) MUST be wrapped in `<LazyMount>` from `src/lib/lazyR3F.tsx`.
- Set `gl={{ antialias: false, powerPreference: "high-performance" }}` on Canvas.
- Use `dpr={[1, 2]}` and clamp manually on `qualityTier === "low"`.

## Reduced motion = no scroll-jacking

When `prefersReducedMotion`, ScrollTrigger pinning is forbidden — replace with ordinary block layout. Transforms tied to `scrub: true` must short-circuit.
